            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to validate finance codes specific to the New York Power Authority (NYPA). It checks whether a given finance code meets certain criteria or exists within a predefined set of valid codes."
